					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Thursday evening news bits from Absor</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=325908" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/044735.html">When Pets Attack! VII: Cynthia and Zebenebar (LD NOT involved)</a></B><P>

Yesterday I was in a group of 4 people hunting Cyclops's and killing Cynthia in Rathe Mountians. We were getting ready to disband when Cynthia popped again and I suggested we kill her one more time. I asked everyone if they were ready and two said yes and the other (a mage) said "Go" as he sent in his petand started to cast a spell. So I hit autoattack, taunt, and bash, all at the same time when I realize that I'm target on the mages pet. So I click over to cynthia and continue. We'd been killing her in about 3-5 seconds so I wasn't too worried that I hadn't been hitting her. Then all of a sudden I see...<P>

Zebenebar slashes you for 8 points of damage. <BR>
Zebenebar tries to slash you but misses.<P>

<B>Seems strange. But it could very well have been the result of you mage losing connection for a short while at the end of the fight (the kind of thing that would look like a lag-spike to the player)...<P>

Still, seems odd.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/044767.html">Absor, Why is this name illegal?</a></B><P>

"You guys are reading the rules literally..."<P>

<B>Well, that is the idea of a rule...<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/044793.html">The death of Necros (Part Two)</a></B><P>

Bonezs wrote: "1) Fix the dot poof problem but until it is fixed tell gms and lead guides to give raiding parties the item they usually get from these mobs if it happens."<P>

<B>Unfortunately there is no way for the GMs to know that a corpse poofed. Asking them to reimburse people for that would leave them far too wide open to being scammed. It should be fixed for any NPC over 54th level already, and we're making a change that should fix most instances of poofing at any level. Yes, if you do all the damage to an NPC and manage to do the killing blow while Lind Dead, the corpse will disappear. That won't change. But nearly all other instances of poofing should be gone as of the next patch, and all of them for over 54th level NPCs should already be gone.</B><P>

"2)Remove skel effect on ignite and chill bones. make them straight dd that can be cast like any other dd."<P>

<B>Well, then it would just be another direct damage spell. That's not particularly interesting. I'm certainly not adverse to suggesting a change, but let's try to come up with something better. It's not going to work, due to the way models are built, that we can just scale the skeleton to the same size and the original creature.</B><P>

"3)Make bond of death 800hp dot resist like wiz lures."<P>

<B>It's a pretty solid bet that only wizards are ever going to get lure spells.</B><P>

"4)Make mana transfer ratio 2:1 instead of 3:1"<P>

<B>This isn't very reasonable either. As I stated, with the ability to turn hit points into mana, and the ability (think bard and chloro) to regain hit points quickly, making the mana transfer ratio better isn't very likely.<P>

More on this later…</B><P>

"5)New spell an Upgrade to ST at 55 we get the prenerf St spell stats back (ie memblur chance) poor mans mezzs."<P>

<B>Screamin terror (by the way, it's very helpful if you avoid using abbreviations…) would be nice if it worked as it was initially intended (fear with a memory blur). But it doesn't appear that this can be done.</B><P>

"6)Fix the new pact spell so it doesnt overwrite sln ect."<P>

<B>This won't happen either. The negative 'regeneration' component of the pact spells has to overwrite skin like nature effect. That's just the way the game code works.</B><P>

"7)Change ebolt to a spell that does same damage but stacks with shamens spells.(hint change all damage spell so they atleast stack with other classes dots)"<P>

<B>This is pretty unlikely. These are the same as the shaman spells, exactly, so they won't stack.</B><P>

"Now for the big ones: 
8)change all lifetaps post 44 to resist similar towiz lures or remove flag from uber mobs."<P>

<B>As I said before, I don't think anyone but wizards are ever going to see a lure spell. And there is no flag on NPCs that makes them specifically immune to Life Tap. Some NPCs just have a very high magic resistance.</B><P>

"9)make dots stack like like dd even if u have to change refresh times so as to balance them out.Not just necros but all classes that use dots."<P>

<B>This also isn't likely to happen. I imagine if it did, we'd have to make all DoTs so weak in order to compensate for the ability to stack them that you wouldn't be very happy with the results. Stacking DoTs is a very powerful thing, and has to be controlled very carefully.</B><P>

"10)If not 9 then atleast give us more dots that do the same dam but different names so in a big group there are more then 4 dots that can be shared between 6 or 7 people."<P>

<B>This is, essentially, the same request as #9, with the same answer.</B><P>

"11)Last one is a wild idea give shamen druids and necro the same 4 dots that are lure: fire cold magic disease .They do 1200 dam in 30 secs but like wiz not all lures work on all mobs.this would help all 3 classes that use dots as there main attack useful."<P>

<B>Sigh… one more time… nobody is likely to get Lure-type spells except for wizards.</B><P>

"12)have a skill for dot casters that cuts by 5% every lvl the amount of time to do max damage."<P>

<B>Interesting idea. But, well, most of your suggestions would increase the power of necromancers in general. Very few of them address the issue that seems to be the real concern. I don't think that anyone can truly tell me that necromancers need anything pre-50th level. And from 51-60 they are great in all ways. The only concern that I've read that I agree with is that they might need more to do (not more power) during the big battle on a raid. Very few of your suggestions address that issue, and I'm not really likely to advocate things that just make necromancers more powerful.<P>

There do seem to be some broken spells, like Track Corpse. But, in general, I think necromancers are pretty rockin.<P>

I did want to point something out. Something that we discovered a short while back.<P>

We were looking at how the Lich spells work, when we discovered something that was, well, a bug.<P>

When we changed the code to reduce spell damage in PvP by 33%, Lich changed with it. What we didn't realize was that Lich is a player doing damage to a player (even though it's a player doing damage to himself). This means that when Lich takes hit point from you, it's only taking 2/3 as many as it should. So you are currently getting a 1 for 1 exchange of hit points for mana with that spell.<P>

We have not decided to repair this bug. It seems that we won't.<P>

But when you're calculating your efficiency, keep this in mind.</B><P>

Azakar wrote: "(*) I was encouraged to hear your thoughts regarding improving pet fear resistance."<P>

<B>Well, don't be too encouraged… Some things were brought to my attention in house and by players as to why this wasn't such a great idea. The obvious one that I missed was that it would completely unbalance PvP as regards necromancers. Also, if we give such a thing to necro pets… yup, we'd be called on to do the same or something similar to all other pets. And, well, that's not really a road down which I want to tread.<P>

The idea isn't totally lost, but it's not being well received, and for reasons that I understand and agree with.</B><P>

"(*) Existing Item Problems. The necromancer epic weapon is mostly useless at epic fights. Epic weapons should not be useless at epic fights. This issue is shared by the druid, necromancer, and shaman ... perhaps others. The necromancer VP weapon cannot be used with lich -- guides have admitted to me that it's broken. It needs to be fixed. Zlandicar's heart, which is supposed to give a really weak regeneration, doesn't even do this currently -- it's broken. This needs to be fixed as well."<P>

<B>I'll mention the VP weapon and the heart to the team.<P>

For now, let's leave the epic thing out of it. Epics aren't likely to change soon.</B><P>

"(*) It saddens me to see my fellow necromancers battling with shadow knights over the upcoming achievement of the Summon Corpse spell by shadow knights. "<P>

<B>I really don't like how giving one thing to one class inevitably brings out a request for something also to be given to another class.<P>

Think about this for a moment. If we add something to a class, it's usually to help bring them up to par with the rest of the classes in some facet, that's the whole idea of balance. Turning around and 'compensating' other classes for this sort of negates the whole balance thing, now doesn't it? IF any of the changes currently on the Test server make it into the game, they will be done on their own merit, and there won't be any 'consolation prizes' for other classes because of them. The whole idea is pretty silly. This isn't a contest.</B><P>

"Like so many have stated, necromancers are NOT here to complain about grouping ability. It is RAIDING ability that we have problems with."<P>

<B>And, again, I'd really like to hear some suggestions that are raid specific. Most of the ones I've seen so far are about increasing the power of a necromancer in general, and have little at all to do with raids. I guess that's why I liked the pet fear thing…<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Ayama wrote: "Ragefire poofed last night, a non-LD wizard got the killing hit...and you say this."<P>

<B>I keep seeing this. This is, so far, the only NPC that people claim has poofed lately (that I know of) that is over 55th level… What server? Did you witness this on?</B><P>

GeistTallon said: "Raids are THE ONLY GAME after lvl 50. If anyone thinks this is not true, please tell me how they get deep into sebilis, charasis, veeshans peak, the planes, Keal, Skyshrine, Western Wastes, Sirens Grotto, Dragon Necropolis, Sleepers Tomb, ect, solo or with a small group."<P>

<B>No, I understand that raids are a part of the game. But they are still a relatively small part. Consider how many hours you spent on raids, and compare that to the hours spent playing your character up to the level you needed to go on those raids.<P>

And even on a raid, fighting the boss mob may be the climax, but it isn't the whole raid. There is a lot more to it than that. In my opinion, a good player will be wanted on a raid because he's good, not because he's a necromancer (or because he isn't a necromancer).<P>

But I'm not saying that your concerns should be ignored because of this. I am talking to you about this because I do think it matters. But too many people are trying to find some way to leverage this discussion to things beyond the point, which is the end of raids. All the way up to the final fight necromancers are wonderfully useful. The focus here is on that last ten or fifteen minutes…</B><P>

Carmageddon said: "Please try Tanarus again - NO!"<P>

<B>Now that’s a shame, 'cause Tan is a great game.</B><P>

Bloodstar1 wrote: "If I understand correctly, one thing that can be done fairly easy is texture colors. I may not have the proper term but it is kind of like all the colored Fine Steel that can be made now. Would it be possible to recolor the mob based on the spell that was cast?"<P>

<B>That's a good idea. I'm not sure, but I don't think it would work, though. I'm pretty sure that, even though the models can be tinted pretty easily, that can't be done on the fly. So to make that work we'd have to make a new, tinted model for every single NPC… That's just too much work for what we're after here.<P>

But I like this idea, and I'll double check my logic with the local artistic types.</B><P>

Misicius wrote: "I still dont understand why mana transfer cant be one to one. The only way I can see that this would double a necromancers mana pool is that because our spells are close to the most inefficient for mana, if not the worst."<P>

<B>Let me try to go over my logic with the whole mana transfer thing. Keep in mind that players will be more creative than me…<P>

But if a necromancer could transfer mana 1:1 then he could throw his mana around at will. Using the Lichy spells, he can convert his hit points 1:1 to mana. So when low on hit points, he can give mana 1:1 to a cleric. A cleric can heal the necromancer at a ratio better than 2:1. In essence, then, the a necromancer working with a cleric could create mana from nothing… and that doesn't even consider regeneration…<P>

I hope that's clear: 1 necromancer hit point becomes 1 necromancer mana, which becomes 1 cleric mana, which is then turned into 2 necromancer hit points, which can become 2 necromancer mana…<P>

It's what Magic: The Gathering players call infinite mana. Usually when that happens, you take your cards and go home. </B><P>

Zotreth Beion`Dhevel wrote: "5. FIX this item!

<B>Clue me in, what's wrong with it?<P>

And can we please stop attacking each other? The usefulness of this thread is dwindling, and I don't see a reason for it. Let's talk ideas, rather than hurling insults at each other.<P>

Alan</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
